Revered Al Sharpton delivered a sermon at Charity Missionary Baptist Church in North Charleston on Sunday morning  . 
  He is expected to attend a vigil for Walter Scott on Sunday afternoon . 
  The civil rights leader addressed the shooting of the black driver by a white police officer . 
  Sharpton preached at the church and praised North Charleston Mayor Keith Summey for firing Michael Slager . 
  He is also expected to speak at the vigil for Scott . 
  Scott was fatally shot by Slager after he fled a traffic stop on Saturday . 
  The reverend addressed the Scott case and the need for reform of policing during his sermon . 
  Elected officials and police from North Charleston were in attendance . 
 